        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 18 at 5:09PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 508 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Yale, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Yale around 515 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Lynn Township, Fargo,
and Brockway.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
